msgid ""
"An `<inputExpression>` inside a decision table is missing a `typeRef` "
"attribute"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Cdmn-validation-reference.md:112
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\reference\\dmn-validation-reference.md:112"
msgid "**Rationale**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Cdmn-validation-reference.md:112
msgid ""
"`typeRef` declares the FEEL type of the input column. Without it, Operaton "
"performs no type coercion — a string `\"true\"` is not automatically cast to "
"`boolean true`, which causes rules to never match if the FEEL type does not "
"align with the runtime variable type. For RONL publishing, typed inputs are "
"required for semantic interoperability."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Cdmn-validation-reference.md:112
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\reference\\dmn-validation-reference.md:112"
msgid "**Fix**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Cdmn-validation-reference.md:112
msgid ""
"Add `typeRef=\"boolean\"` (or `string`, `integer`, `date`, etc.) to the "
"`<inputExpression>`."
msgstr ""

