msgid "No element in the document has an attribute in the CPRMV namespace"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Cdmn-validation-reference.md:211
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\reference\\dmn-validation-reference.md:211"
msgid "**Rationale**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Cdmn-validation-reference.md:211
msgid ""
"CPRMV attributes are the mechanism by which a DMN file records its "
"connection to Dutch legislation. Without them, the exported Turtle will "
"contain no legal provenance metadata. The issue is `info` rather than "
"`warning` because a DMN may be published to TriplyDB as a technical artefact "
"before CPRMV metadata has been added."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Cdmn-validation-reference.md:211
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\reference\\dmn-validation-reference.md:211"
msgid "**Fix**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Creference%5Cdmn-validation-reference.md:211
msgid ""
"Add CPRMV namespace declaration to `<definitions>`: `xmlns:cprmv=\"https://"
"cprmv.open-regels.nl/0.3.0/\"`, then add attributes such as "
"`cprmv:rulesetType`, `cprmv:ruleType`, and `cprmv:confidence` to your "
"decision elements."
msgstr ""

